sentences: Lawrence Rothman (born June 19, 1982) is an American singer-songwriter based in Los Angeles.
Their debut album The Book of Law was released on October 13, 2017 via Downtown Records/Interscope.
From 2002 to 2011, Rothman fronted the punk rock band Living Things under the name Lillian Berlin.
In June 2013, Rothman released their debut single, "Montauk Fling", with an accompanying video directed by Sigismondi.
Throughout 2013, Rothman released subsequent singles on Mamaroma: “#1 All Time Low”, “Kevin”, and “Fatal Attraction”.
In 2014, Rothman signed to Downtown Records and began work on their debut album, The Book of Law, with producer Justin Raisen.

sentences: "My Woman" as well as acting with their first role in Drake Doremus' Endings, Beginnings, premiering at the 2019 Toronto International Film Festival.
In November 2019 it was announced that Rothman produced and wrote the soundtrack for DreamWorks Pictures The Turning.
Rothman authored a book Postmortem Bliss, which was turned into a short film for Tuner Classics in 2006.
In 2019, Rothman launched their own record label, KRO Records, with Justin Raisen, Yves Rothman and Thomas Winkler.
Other releases in 2019 included Kills Birds’ self-titled debut LP, Buzzy Lee’s (Sasha Spielberg) EP, “Close Encounters of Our Own Kind”, and a single titled “Mother” by Courtney Love.
In 2020, KRO Records released Steven Spielberg produced "The Turning" soundtrack under exclusive license to Sony Music Entertainment.
In 2010, Rothman scored The Runaways, a biopic film on the Joan Jett fronted female rock band
In 2017, Rothman scored the News Emmy nominated New York Times Great Performers 2017 series short films starring Nicole Kidman, Timothy Chalamet, Saoirse Ronan, Jake Gyllenhaal and more.
In 2018, Rothman scored a short film on the life of occult filmmaker Kenneth Anger for Gucci and Systems Magazine.
From a young age, Rothman identified as gender-fluid, wearing makeup and presenting in an androgynous style.
